{
  "texts": [
    "To make quantum development more accessible and efficient, it's crucial that these circuits are designed to be as reusable as possible.",
    "By creating quantum circuits that can be reused across multiple algorithms and applications, the overall effort required to develop new quantum solutions is significantly reduced.",
    "Reusability in quantum software not only saves time and resources but also enables developers to build upon existing, well-optimized circuits rather than starting from scratch each time a new algorithm is needed.For circuits to be reusable, they must also be composable, meaning they can be integrated with other circuits seamlessly.",
    "This is where the current landscape of quantum development faces a challenge.",
    "The tools and frameworks available to support circuit composition and reuse are still in their infancy, lacking the sophistication seen in classical software engineering."
  ]
}